Interface ISlotEditor


  • public interface ISlotEditor
    Provides mechanisms for editing a specific ISlot object.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      Re-sets the cardinality of the slot, by resetting the cardinality for the associated slot-type.

    • Method Detail

      • setValueType

        boolean setValueType(CValue<?> valueType)
        Re-sets the value-type for the slot, by resetting the value-type for the associated slot-type.

        NOTE: The associated slot-type will always be a local copy of the instantiated slot-type, and hence any edits will only affect the particular slot.

        Parameters:
        valueType - New value-type for slot
        Returns:
        True if value-type has been updated.

      • setCardinality

        boolean setCardinality(CCardinality cardinality)
        Re-sets the cardinality of the slot, by resetting the cardinality for the associated slot-type.

        NOTE: The associated slot-type will always be a local copy of the instantiated slot-type, and hence any edits will only affect the particular slot.

        Parameters:
        cardinality - Cardinality to set
        Returns:
        True if cardinality has been updated.

      • setActivation

        boolean setActivation(CActivation activation)
        Re-sets the activation of the slot, by resetting the activation for the associated slot-type.

        NOTE: The associated slot-type will always be a local copy of the instantiated slot-type, and hence any edits will only affect the particular slot.

        Parameters:
        activation - Activation to set
        Returns:
        True if activation has been updated.

      • setEditability

        boolean setEditability(IEditability editability)
        Re-sets the editability of the slot, by resetting the relevant component ("assertions" or "queries") of the editability for the associated slot-type.

        NOTE: The associated slot-type will always be a local copy of the instantiated slot-type, and hence any edits will only affect the particular instance of the slot.

        Parameters:
        editability - Assertions-editability to set
        Returns:
        True if slot-type editability has been updated.

      • updateFixedValues

        boolean updateFixedValues(java.util.List<IValue> fixedValues)
        Updates the "fixed" value-list for the slot, so that it contains each of the specified values, and only those values, making any required additions and deletions, and then updating the current value-list accordingly. Where relevant, will maintain the current fixed value-list ordering in preference to the supplied list.
        Parameters:
        fixedValues - New fixed values for slot
        Returns:
        True if fixed values set has been updated
